      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So you're saying the tension and the specific foods like fried chicken are basically shorthand for their struggles and economic background? If I were to write a scene where the family was actually doing really well—like, maybe they're upper class or just very stable—would you still include those same elements, or does the \"realness\" of a Black family dinner inherently require that sense of struggle and those specific staple foods?",
